how do i get my puppy to stop chewing on her name tag i used to have a dog that loved to chew things we got him this stuff called bitter apple it is in a green and yellow bottle and found at many pet stores it is not harmful to your puppy it just tastes really bad to her just take off her collar and spray the bitter apple on it outside as to not get it on her toys and give her the wrong idea let it sit there for about minutes and put her collar back on hopefully this helps good luck Dog training Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Fancy rat Hamster Dog Fanta Sick Puppy Labrador Retriever Care Bears Hey Jude Skinny Puppy Spot the Dog Dog collar Pet skunk Nintendogs Apple Shaggy dog story Plastic Bottle Rocket (film) Toy Domestic rabbit Beethoven (film) The Fairly OddParents One Tree Hill (TV series) Housebreaking Lady and the Tramp World War Three (Doctor Who) Neighbours Docking Mojave people Wild at Heart (Buffy episode) Puppy mill The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe B-side Dollar store Potato The Grim Adventures of Billy and Mandy Jackass: The Movie Neopets Tag Tobacco Tooth Christmas tree Frugivore Steve Jobs Fair use Kim Possible Crate training The Adventures of Pete & Pete Garfield Luck Invader Zim Halitosis Bong Manual transmission Pet store KaBlam! Dog breed Extraordinary Machine Majin Buu Saga Ron Weasley Tooth enamel Clancy Wiggum Socialization Trademark Bulk vending Coffee Philip J. Fry Martini cocktail Ferret Cuisine of Denmark Aztec Objective-C Basic English Resident Evil Outbreak Vegeta Kodocha The Inside MP3 Golden Retriever 101 Dalmatians: The Series Sake Collar FoxTrot Pitaten Karma Trailer Park Boys Bacon Guinea pig Compact audio cassette Beer Yarrow Incarnations of Immortality Looney Tunes and Merrie Melodies filmography Color User Friendly Weebl and Bob Chewing gum Ringo Starr Professional wrestling match types 